## When to use
When you need an overview of your system's overall resource utilization and want detailed statistics on memory usage, process activity, and disk I/O.

## Approach
Utilize the `shell_exec` tool to execute the `vmstat` command, which provides comprehensive information about system resources. This approach allows for monitoring various metrics such as processes (procs), memory usage (memory), swap space utilization, I/O statistics, system activity (system), and CPU activity (cpu). Advanced users can interpret detailed output to understand system bottlenecks.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "vmstat 1"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run a shell command that displays system resource usage metrics at one-second intervals, providing real-time monitoring capabilities.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure necessary utilities like `vmstat` are installed on your system.
- Be cautious about interpreting output correctly with complex workloads and varying system configurations.